I feel so lucky to have found blogging back in 2011, which led me to where I am today, designing and creating dresses at @galmeetsglam 🌸 life is a crazy journey. As a college student studying marketing, I always had a love for fashion but never saw an opportunity or path to be able to work in the industry. It seemed untouchable and out of my reach. I settled on just loving clothes. I’ve always loved clothes. Design and style is part of who I am, and I always knew that no matter what I was doing or where I was at in life, I could show who I was and what I wanted to be through what I was wearing. Fast forward to last year when we launched @galmeetsglam after spending four years building it. I finally felt like I found my calling in life, like I was doing exactly what I was meant to be doing. It brings me so much joy to design. To bring a vision to life and to work with our team day to day to create something unique and beautiful. We are a very tiny design team, but what you don’t see are all of the hands that touch the product before it comes to market. I have so much more respect and appreciation for clothes after actually spending the past few years learning how everything works. So today, for #nationaldressday I am not only grateful to be able to design and create these dresses but I am MOST thankful for the amazing group of people who bring them to life and into our customers hands! 💕 #dresslover #ilovedresses #gmgonme #gmgcollection

Thomas and I have been watching a lot of @themontydon recently. We started with his Italian Gardens series and then got hooked on Big Dreams, Small Spaces. What a fantastic show that leaves you feeling so happy and inspired. I love hearing how plants and gardens bring each person a unique sense of joy and pride. I know @tberolz and I feel the same way, we both have a special place in our hearts for them. Thomas is much more patient than I am. He loves taking his time and will spend hours making sure it’s done right. I wish I could say I was the same. One of my goals for this year is to spend more time in our yard and garden. We have big goals for our backyard and right now it’s mostly a complete mess with a giant shed smack in the middle making it feel much smaller than it is. It’s going to take a lot of work but I’m excited to start working on it and see it come to life! Right now we’re spending lots of time researching to understand what will grow best where and why. If there’s one thing we’ve learned from Monty, it’s to always do your research and understand what you’re growing. This picture is from the stunning Hampstead Heath gardens last spring #gardens #flowers

I can’t wait for NYE to pull out another @galmeetsglam dress! It feels so surreal to finally be able to celebrate so many special occasions in the dresses I always dreamed of, especially after years (more than four) of trying to get the brand to launch. It did not come without many times being told “no”, or that I didn’t know what I was doing, or that I should just create something that’s “trendy” and “what sells”. There were many tears and moments when I thought it would never happen. BUT, I never doubted myself and what I wanted to create. Our launch collection in April was still the same of what I wanted to create back in 2014. It never wavered and I never gave into the pressures around me telling me otherwise. The most amazing part? The reaction from so many of you who felt that this was missing in the market too- classic, feminine dresses that you want to reach for over and over again. These dresses mean so much more to me than just a piece of clothing. They’re my heart and soul, my personality and passion and what I truly believe in. So thank you for believing in me too. There is truly no greater gift than to see the connection that our customers have with our dresses. Thank you a million times and happy holidays! I hope you get to celebrate in a #gmgcollection dress! 🎉 #gmgonme

Growing up one year and three days apart, naturally made us very close from the moment we met. Right from the very beginning, we were best friends and it’s stayed that way all twenty something years of our lives.
